## 2. `frontend/src/components/UploadForm.tsx`

File upload form with drag-and-drop:
- Use `react-dropzone` for drag-and-drop
- Accept only .pdf and .docx files (validate client-side before submit)
- Show selected filename once chosen
- Optional job description textarea (max 10,000 chars, show char count)
- 'Analyze' button — disabled while loading
- On submit: build FormData with cv_file and job_description (if non-empty), call submitMutation
- Show inline validation errors (wrong file type before submit)
- Show server error if submitMutation.error is set

Props:
```typescript
interface UploadFormProps {
  onSubmit: (formData: FormData) => void;
  isLoading: boolean;
  error: ApiError | null;
}
```

Styling with Tailwind: clean, minimal. Upload area with dashed border, file icon, 'Drop your CV here or click to browse' text. Button: blue, full-width on mobile.

