## 4. `frontend/src/components/ScoreGauge.tsx`

Visual display of seniority score:
- Use `recharts` RadialBarChart or simple circular progress
- Show the total score as a large number (e.g. '72')
- Color coding: 0-33 red, 34-66 amber, 67-100 green (use text labels too, not just color)
- Seniority label below score: 0-34='Junior', 35-59='Mid-level', 60-79='Senior', 80-100='Lead/Principal'
- Sub-score breakdown table below:
  | Category | Score | Max |
  |----------|-------|-----|
  | Experience | 25 | 30 |
  | Skills | 22 | 30 |
  | Education | 15 | 20 |
  | Role Seniority | 10 | 20 |
- Show justification strings from `score_breakdown.justifications` as small grey text under each row
- Show 'Job-fit adjusted' badge if `job_fit_adjusted` is true

Props:
```typescript
interface ScoreGaugeProps {
  score: number;
  breakdown: ScoreBreakdown;
}
```

